rsInfoModule.description: The MIB module describes various tunnel objects of RapidStream system.

rsIpsecTunnelMIB.name: rsIpsecTunnelMIB
rsIpsecTunnelMIB.description: This is the base object identifier for all tunnel branches.

rsIpsecTunnel.name: rsIpsecTunnel
rsIpsecTunnel.description: This is the base object identifier for all tunnel information.

rsIpsecTunnelNum.name: rsIpsecTunnelNum
rsIpsecTunnelNum.description: The total number of entries in the rsIpsecTunnelTable.

rsIpsecTunnelTable.name: rsIpsecTunnelTable
rsIpsecTunnelTable.description: This is the connection table describing all current tunnels exist on this entity.

rsIpsecTunnelEntry.name: rsIpsecTunnelEntry
rsIpsecTunnelEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a tunnel between two security gateways.

rsIpsecTunnelID.name: rsIpsecTunnelID
rsIpsecTunnelID.description: The running index of this tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelLocalAddr.name: rsIpsecTunnelLocalAddr
rsIpsecTunnelLocalAddr.description: The local IP address of the current tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelPeerAddr.name: rsIpsecTunnelPeerAddr
rsIpsecTunnelPeerAddr.description: The remote IP address of the current tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelInSpi.name: rsIpsecTunnelInSpi
rsIpsecTunnelInSpi.description: The security parameters index of inbound SA's within this tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelOutSpi.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutSpi
rsIpsecTunnelOutSpi.description: The security parameters index of outbound SA's within this tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelCreateTime.name: rsIpsecTunnelCreateTime
rsIpsecTunnelCreateTime.description: The date and time when the tunnel is created.

rsIpsecTunnelDeviceID.name: rsIpsecTunnelDeviceID
rsIpsecTunnelDeviceID.description: The identifier of target device where the SA resides.

rsIpsecTunnelEspEncryptAlg.name: rsIpsecTunnelEspEncryptAlg
rsIpsecTunnelEspEncryptAlg.description: The encryption algorithm used in the tunnel. It's 0 if ESP is not used.

rsIpsecTunnelEspAuthAlg.name: rsIpsecTunnelEspAuthAlg
rsIpsecTunnelEspAuthAlg.description: The authentication algorithm used in the tunnel. It's 0 if ESP is not used.

rsIpsecTunnelAhAuthAlg.name: rsIpsecTunnelAhAuthAlg
rsIpsecTunnelAhAuthAlg.description: The AH authentication algorithm used in the tunnel. It's 0 if AH is not used.

rsIpsecTunnelMode.name: rsIpsecTunnelMode
rsIpsecTunnelMode.description: The tunnel/transport mode of the tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelKeyMode.name: rsIpsecTunnelKeyMode
rsIpsecTunnelKeyMode.description: The key mode of the tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelLifeTime.name: rsIpsecTunnelLifeTime
rsIpsecTunnelLifeTime.description: The life time (in hundredths of a second) of the tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelLifeLength.name: rsIpsecTunnelLifeLength
rsIpsecTunnelLifeLength.description: The maximum traffic in bytes that the tunnel is allowed to support.

rsIpsecTunnelInSaBytes.name: rsIpsecTunnelInSaBytes
rsIpsecTunnelInSaBytes.description: Current active inbound SA bytes of the tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelOutSaBytes.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutSaBytes
rsIpsecTunnelOutSaBytes.description: Current active outbound SA bytes of the tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelAccSecs.name: rsIpsecTunnelAccSecs
rsIpsecTunnelAccSecs.description: The number of seconds that the tunnel has existed.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorProtocol.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorProtocol
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorProtocol.description: The ip protocol number that this SA selector carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPType.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPType
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPType.description: The type of remote IP address of the SA selector in the entity.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPOne.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPOne
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPOne.description: The first remote IP address of the SA selector in the entity. It's IP address if remote IP of this selector only has one address. It's IP address of subnet if the remote IP of this selector is IP subnet. It's the start IP address if the remote IP of this selector has a range of addresses.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPTwo.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPTwo
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemoteIPTwo.description: The second remote IP address of the SA selector in the entity. It's 0 if remote IP of this selector only has one address. It's netmask of subnet if the remote IP of this selector is IP subnet. It's the end IP address if the remote IP of this selector has a range of addresses.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemotePort.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemotePort
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorRemotePort.description: The remote port used by this selector in the entity.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPType.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPType
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPType.description: The type of local IP address of the SA selector in the entity.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPOne.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPOne
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPOne.description: The first local IP address of the SA selector in the entity. It's IP address if local IP of this selector only has one address. It's IP address of subnet if the local IP of this selector is IP subnet. It's the start IP address if the local IP of this selector has a range of IP addresses.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPTwo.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPTwo
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalIPTwo.description: The second local IP address of the SA selector in the entity. It's 0 if local IP of this selector only has one address. It's netmask of subnet if the local IP of this selector is IP subnet. It's the end IP address if the local IP of this selector has a range of IP addresses.

rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalPort.name: rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalPort
rsIpsecTunnelSelectorLocalPort.description: The local port used by this selector in the entity.

rsIpsecTunnelNumRekey.name: rsIpsecTunnelNumRekey
rsIpsecTunnelNumRekey.description: The number of rekeys of the tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelInKbytes.name: rsIpsecTunnelInKbytes
rsIpsecTunnelInKbytes.description: Total inbound traffic in Kbytes since the establish of this tunnel.

rsIpsecTunnelOutKbytes.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutKbytes
rsIpsecTunnelOutKbytes.description: Total outound traffic in Kbytes since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelInPackets.name: rsIpsecTunnelInPackets
rsIpsecTunnelInPackets.description: Total number of inbound packets since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelOutPackets.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutPackets
rsIpsecTunnelOutPackets.description: Total number of outound packets since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelInDecryptErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelInDecryptErrors
rsIpsecTunnelInDecryptErrors.description: Total number of packets discarded due to decryption error since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelInAuthErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelInAuthErrors
rsIpsecTunnelInAuthErrors.description: Total number of packets discarded due to authentication error since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelInReplayErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelInReplayErrors
rsIpsecTunnelInReplayErrors.description: Total number of packets discarded due to replay error since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelInOtherErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelInOtherErrors
rsIpsecTunnelInOtherErrors.description: The number of packets discarded due to errors other than decryption, authentication or replay errors. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of receive buffers, and may include packets dropped due to congestion at the decryption element.

rsIpsecTunnelOutDecryptErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutDecryptErrors
rsIpsecTunnelOutDecryptErrors.description: Total number of packets discarded due to decryption error since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelOutAuthErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutAuthErrors
rsIpsecTunnelOutAuthErrors.description: Total number of packets discarded due to authentication error since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelOutReplayErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutReplayErrors
rsIpsecTunnelOutReplayErrors.description: Total number of packets discarded due to replay error since the establish of this connection.

rsIpsecTunnelOutOtherErrors.name: rsIpsecTunnelOutOtherErrors
rsIpsecTunnelOutOtherErrors.description: The number of packets discarded due to errors other than decryption, authentication or replay errors. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of receive buffers, and may include packets dropped due to congestion at the decryption element.

rsIpsecTunnelUdpEncap.name: rsIpsecTunnelUdpEncap
rsIpsecTunnelUdpEncap.description: Indicates whether if UDP encapsulated IPSec has been enabled.

rsIpsecTunnelPeerUdpPort.name: rsIpsecTunnelPeerUdpPort
rsIpsecTunnelPeerUdpPort.description: The peer's UDP port of current tunnel when UDP encapsulated IPSec is enabled.

rsIpsecTunnelOrigPeerAddr.name: rsIpsecTunnelOrigPeerAddr
rsIpsecTunnelOrigPeerAddr.description: The original peer ip address of current tunnel when UDP encapsulated IPSec is enabled
